tool.name: MO_tool

param.name: SELongStr
param.dialogReference: Longitude of SE corner of map rectangle. May be in decimal degrees (-120.625), degrees - decimal minutes (-120 37.5) or degrees - minutes seconds (-120 37 30). West longitudes (all of US) are negative.

param.name: SELatStr
param.dialogReference: Latitude of SE corner of map rectangle. May be in decimal degrees (42.375), degrees - decimal minutes (42 22.5) or degrees - minutes seconds (48 22 30). South latitudes (none in US) are negative.

param.name: dLong
param.dialogReference:
E-W extent of map rectangle. Values <= 5 are assumed to be in degrees. Values >5 are assumed to be in minutes. Enter 600 to obtain a 10 degree extent.

Default = 7.5

param.name: dLat
param.dialogReference:
N-S extent of map rectangle. Values <= 5 are assumed to be in degrees. Values >5 are assumed to be in minutes. Enter 600 to obtain a 10 degree extent.

Default = 7.5

param.name: isNAD27
param.dialogReference: Check to locate map boundary and tics at NAD27 lat-long positions. Uncheck to locate at NAD83 positions.

param.name: outgdb
param.dialogReference: Must be an existing, writable geodatabase. Please do not select a feature dataset or feature class (though ArcGIS will let you do so).

param.name: outSpRef
param.dialogReference: Browse to select coordinate system from ArcGISprovided coordinate system definitions, to import a coordinate system from an existing data set (RECOMMENDED) or define a coordinate system from scratch.

param.name: scratch
param.dialogReference:
Directory that is writable. Files xxxbox.csv, xxxtics.csv, xxx1.dbf, xxx1.dbf.xml will be written to this directory and then deleted. Existing files with these names will be lost!

Must be a folder, not a Geodatabase.

tool.summary: Calculates map boundary and tics for rectangular (in lat-long space) areas. Boundaries and tics may be in NAD27 or NAD83, and are projected to output coordinate system. Output feature classes MapOutline and Tics are written to top level of output geodatabase. Any existing feature classes with these names will be overwritten.
